<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Deathbane27</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have seen this discussed several times with getting DXwindows to work with this problem, but not with this situation before, so here goes:<P>Problem:  When running EQ in DXwindows, all I can see is sky.<P>Graphics card:  ATI All-in-Wonder 128, AGP, 16 MB.  Running on a motherboard with a *shudder* VIA *shudder* chipset.  *shudder*<P>Has anyone been able to get DXwindows to work with an ATI card?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bubba</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I run an ATI Rage Fury 128.<P>It works.<P>Bubba</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bush</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Works on my Nvidia GEforce 256   <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">k7</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Don't forget to kill mip mapping in EQ, and make sure your desktop is set to 16 bit color.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">alien</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ashran or anyone have some suggestions to try besides mipmapping off and 16-bit color?  DirectX 7.0a updated, then updated to latest video drivers. (They ain't that recent since Number Nine is out of business.)<P>I have the blue sky problem too, but with a Number Nine video card (Revolution IV with 32 mb of RAM).  At character select screen, everything is fine except no character model.<P>dxWindows was crashing with no error message when trying to go from splash screen to character select screen before I turned mipmapping off.<P>Mipmapping off, same resolution on<BR>both Kunark and Velious installed and enabled<BR>Desktop has always been at 16 colors, with 1158x1052 resolution<BR>EQ set to 800x600<BR>DirectX 7.0a under Win98SE<BR>32 mb Number Nine Revolution IV video card<BR>256 mb of 5 nanosecond RAM<BR>P2 450<BR>SCSI<P>It sure seems to grind my hard drive to use EQ inside dxwindows.<P>I am extremely reluctant to move to DirectX 8, given the very haphazard results with EQ and DirectX so far (does Verant have anyone who actually understands their own code?) and other issues.<P>-ac</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">alien</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ashran, or anyone who can help with the blue sky problem?  This is not a Glide video card.<P>Thanks.<P>-alien</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">alien</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't think it's frivolous to bump this thread so it gets some attention.<P>Already read dx windows for dummies thread and pretty much all the other dx windows threads but couldn't see anything helpful.<P>Not a glide video card.  I have tons of RAM, tons of memory on the video card too.  P2 450 should be able to keep up.  Tried various in-game settings.<P>Still have the "blue sky problem".  :-&lt;<P>-alien</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">coolhp</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This might be out ou line guys but : Have you tried DirectX8 or 8.0a.<BR>I have a Win2k machine with an ATI AIW 128 runnin DXWindows and it works fine.<BR>That as well as changing you desktop resolution and please do post here if it works... its seems to be a very common question around here.<P>/wave </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">alien</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Desktop resolution is 16-color and 1152x768, same settings for about two years.  I did try 1024x desktop resolution but that didn't help.  I tried in-game resolutions of 640x480, 800x600, and 1024x and they made no difference.<P>I really, really don't want to try DirectX 8 because of the difficulty of going back to 7 if there are problems.  And I've read way too many horror stories of EQ problems after people have tried 8.<P>Since I have 256 mb of RAM, it really makes me wonder why I hear my hard drive thrashing quite a lot when trying to run EQ inside DX Windows.<P>Ashran, I'll be at the San Diego Fan Faire and look forward to meeting you, as well as thanking you in person for all that you've contributed to the EQ player community.  (That isn't sarcasm about the DX Windows problems, that is meant sincerely because of all you've done in the last two years.)<P>-alien</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
